<h2>Nokia E51 Manual Setup</h2>
<ul class="data">
    <li>
    <p>
        To set up your phone manually you need to go through the following steps:
    </p>
    <p>
        Go to the main menu, select "Tools" and open "Sync". Press "Options" and then 
        "New sync profile". If you are prompted for "Copy values from profile X?" press "No".
    </p>
    
        <p>
          - Enter "7am" in "Sync profile name"<br />
      - Choose "Connection settings"<br />
            - Enter following data:<br />
        - Server version: <b>1.1</b><br />
        - data bearer: <b>Internet</b><br />
        - access point: <b>choose your GPRS, WAP or Wireless settings</b><br />
        - host address: <b>http://sync.7.am</b><br />
        - port: <b>8080</b><br />
        - user name: <b><%= "#{@p.user.login}@#{SITE_NAME}" %></b><br />
        - password: <b>your 7.am password</b><br />
        - Allow sync request: <b>Yes</b><br />
        - Accept all sync reqs.: <b>No</b><br />
        - network authentic.: <b>No</b><br /><br />
            - Press "Back" and choose "Application". Please set up contacts like this:<br />
        - Include in sync: <b>yes</b><br />
        - Remote database: <b>con</b><br />
        - Synchronization type: <b>Normal</b><br />
      <br />
            To start synchronisation go back to the Sync menu and press <b>"Options"</b> and <b>"Synchronise"</b>
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
